name: in the name of pop art
description:
warhol created a genre where pop art would be very popular with his fans. he created myths about popular culture beliefs and also his big name so that people are willing to spend money for a work that is produced a lot.

I don't know why it became the new normal in those days. maybe people are afraid to miss out. people with a culture of consumerism buy the work that warhol created. totally unreasonable at the time. but now it's starting to become natural and reasonable.
